On Today’s show I tackled the multitude of issue surrounding the illegal immigration problem which has skyrocket out of control thanks to President Obama’s policy to ignore the current law when it comes to deporting these folks. Instead he has unilaterally imposed the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals (DACA). This is illegal as the executive branch not only is ignoring the law but making law up on it’s own in violation of the separation of powers clearly outline in the Constitution.

The U.S. Constitution in Article 1 section 8 state the Congress set immigration and naturalization laws as well as write all laws. In the section that deals with Presidential duties the actions he can take on bills is to sign then once passed by both the House and Senate or veto the bill. But, he can not ignore passed law, or create his own laws as some Imperial King.

On the show today we had Patrice Lynes the organizer behind the protests that are taking place in Murrieta, CA Immigration. S Detention Center. She and her group have turned three groups of immigrants that have been flown into San Diego, CA and then bused to the Detention Center in Murrieta. Patrice has great shared a wealth of knowledge with us today on what she has seen and heard on the front lines. A source has revealed to her that five of the Murrieta ICE agents who where sent down to stations closer to the border to process the illegals that have been turned away by protestors have contracted scabies thanks to the poor health screening protocols being followed at detention centers and holding facilitates. In addition her source has revealed that several children have fevers and are coughing blood indicating Tuberculosis a deadly lung disease which is highly contagious. There are suspected infections of bird flu within the illegal population.

Patrice Lynes is willing to guide anyone who wants to start a group in their area of the country as the illegals are being shipped all over the country. So send her an e-mail @ patrice.lynes@gmail.com if you want to discuss what has worked for her group.

